# Week 2 Project Rule

- Keep edits inside `HCDE530_week2_project` unless explicitly asked otherwise.
- Treat `demo_responses.csv` as the source of truth; do not rewrite CSV values unless requested.
- For `demo_word_count.py`:
  - Keep logic beginner-friendly and clearly commented.
  - Use small helper functions for reusable text-processing tasks.
  - Protect summary stats against empty datasets before using `min`, `max`, or averages.
- For `dashboard.html`:
  - Keep it runnable as a single local file with no build step.
  - Prefer plain JavaScript and readable DOM code over framework-style abstractions.
  - Escape/sanitize text before inserting it into HTML.
- When making UI or analysis changes, preserve existing behavior unless the prompt asks for a redesign.
